  keywords = {Mental representations,Semantic distance latency test,Social status},
  pages = {49--57},
  annote = {This study measures the distance effect on social (university ranks, military ranks) and non-social (number) hierarchies. The results suggest that the distance effect operates in analogical ways for both social and non-social variables. Over-all the conclusion is that the effect is due to similar processing and not task-difficulty. This is supported f.i. by the non-correlation of accuracy and reaction-time for military ranks. \\
In addition, familiarity with a variable seems to alter the processing-speed of comparisons on this variable.}
